"meanings":["German: variant of   Abt  .","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): habitational name from Apt, the Yiddish name of Opatów in Świętokrzyskie Voivodeship, Poland. The placename (in German, Yiddish, and Polish) is from a root meaning ‘abbot’, the place having been named for the local abbey. Compare   Abt  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Abt","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Helmut, Horst, Johann, Kurt.","German and Dutch: from Middle Low German or Middle Dutch <i>abt</i> ‘abbot’, hence a metonymic occupational name for a servant of an abbot or a nickname for someone thought to resemble an abbot in some way. In some instances it may have been a topographic or habitational name referring to a house named with this word.","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): variant of   Abt  , a habitational name from Opatów in Poland."]},{"name":"Apter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Avrohom, Bronya, Eliezer, Naftali.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone from Apt (see   Apt  ).","English: habitational name from Aptor in Marldon, Devon, composed of Old English <i>uppe</i> ‘up, above’ + <i>torr</i> ‘rocky outcrop’."]}]},{"name":"Gronwy","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Welsh:  see  Gronow  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Gronow","meanings":["Welsh: relationship name from the Welsh personal name  <i>Goronwy</i> (also found as  <i>Gronw</i> and  <i>Gronow</i>, from Old Welsh  <i>Guorgonui</i>)."]}]},{"name":"Iorwerth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional: from <i>iōr</i>‘ ‘lord’ + a mutated form of <i>berth</i> ‘handsome’; borne in the <i>Mabinogi</i> by the jealous brother of  Madawg , son of  Maredudd . <i>Iorwerth</i> came to be regarded as a Welsh equivalent of  Edward , but it has no actual connection with that name."],"variants":[{"name":"Yorath","meanings":["Anglicized form of   Iorwerth   or, in some cases, a transferred use of the surname derived from it."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Iorwerth Swdrgrin ap Gronwy of Powys was born in Denbighshire, Wales as the son of Gronwy ap Hwfa ap Ithel Felyn of Powys and unknown. He had at least 1 daughter with unknown."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1160–Male":"1160–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1002–Female":"1002–Surnud","1130–Male":"1130–Surnud","1002":"1002","about 1002":"umbes 1002","1130":"1130","1160":"1160","Denbighshire, Wales":"Denbighshire, Wales"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1160–Male":"1160–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1002–Female":"1002–Kuollut","1130–Male":"1130–Kuollut","1002":"1002","about 1002":"noin 1002","1130":"1130","1160":"1160","Denbighshire, Wales":"Denbighshire, Wales"},"fr":{"–":"Décédé","1160–Male":"1160–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1002–Female":"1002–Décédée","1130–Male":"1130–Décédé","1002":"1002","about 1002":"environ 1002","1130":"1130","1160":"1160","Denbighshire, Wales":"Denbighshire, Galles","lifeSummary":"Iorwerth Swdrgrin ap Gronwy of Powys est né à Denbighshire, Galles, fils de Gronwy ap Hwfa ap Ithel Felyn of Powys et unknown. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec unknown."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1160–Male":"1160–Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1002–Female":"1002–Verstorben","1130–Male":"1130–Verstorben","1002":"1002","about 1002":"um 1002","1130":"1130","1160":"1160","Denbighshire, Wales":"Denbighshire, Wales","lifeSummary":"Iorwerth Swdrgrin ap Gronwy of Powys wurde in Denbighshire, Wales, als Sohn von Gronwy ap Hwfa ap Ithel Felyn of Powys und unknown geboren. Er hatte mit unknown mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","1160–Male":"1160–Desede","–Male":"Desede","–Female":"Desede","1002–Female":"1002–Desede","1130–Male":"1130–Desede","1002":"1002","about 1002":"about 1002","1130":"1130","1160":"1160","Denbighshire, Wales":"Denbighshire, Wales"},"hu":{"–":"elhunyt","1160–Male":"1160–e